                            "termSource": null,
                            "termAccession": ""
                        },
                        "description": "<p>Mass spectrometric detection was performed using a Q Exactive HF-X (Thermo Fisher Scientific, USA) equipped with an Electrospray Ionization (ESI) ion source, operating in both positive and negative ESI (+/-) modes. Full MS-data dependent MS/MS (Full MS-ddMS2) mode was employed with the following parameters: sheath gas flow rate of 30 arb, auxiliary gas flow rate of 10 arb, spray voltage set to 3.50 kV for ESI(+) and -2.50 kV for ESI(-), capillary temperature at 325 \u00b0C. The full MS scans were performed with a resolving power of 60,000 FWHM, spanning a mass-to-charge ratio range of 81-1000 m/z. Depended on the full MS scan data, the top 8 precursor ions with the highest intensity were selected for further MS/MS fragmentation, with dynamic exclusion applied to remove unnecessary MS/MS information. Higher-energy collisional dissociation (HCD) was utilized for further MS/MS fragmentation, with a normalized collision energy set to 30% and a resolving power of 15,000 FWHM.</p>",
