                        },
                        "description": "<p>In untargeted metabolomics analysis, the raw MS data were converted to mzXML format by MSConvert in ProteoWizard software package69 (v3.0) and processed by XCMS70 (v3.2) for peak picking and alignment. The XCMS settings were as follows: method = \u201ccentWave\u201d, ppm = 15, peakwidth = c(5,30), mzwid = 0.015, mzdiff = 0.01, and bw = 2. The peak areas of all detected ions were normalized according to robust locally-estimated scatterplot smoothing (LOESS) signal correction71 based on QC samples (Details for QC sample are available in SI). After normalization, the ion peaks with relative standard deviations &gt; 30% in the in all QC samples were deleted.</p>",
